{
  "stem": "11611.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had been a member of the Communist Party from the age of 14 on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His wife immediately sued him for an annulment, although they had two kids by this time had been married about 10 years, on the ground that he deceived her as to his political beliefs-- which worked in New York.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These were the days when you only got divorced by annulment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She was a member of the Communist Party from the age of 14, too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyhow, I-- I talked to Werber at some length and he-- he let me off the hook.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was really in trouble with him, because he started by wanting me as counsel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he had this tremendously concocted story, which he was prepared to represent in court.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I told him I would not represent him on what I knew to be a bunch of lies, that's all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we finally parted ways.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, under extreme circumstances, if he couldn't get a decent appointment, I'd still come back and represent him, because I was a friend of his.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he then got Roger Robb appointed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Robb subsequently is a court of the US Court of Appeals here, and was notoriously conservative and right wing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he got along very well with Robb, and Robb was prepared to defend him to the hilt on this concocted story until, I think, one day the prosecution took Robb aside, showed him photographs of Werber here, there, and elsewhere.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had built up a pretty complete case so Robb finally pleaded him guilty and Werber got, I think, something like an eight or 10-year sentence.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw him when he went to jail.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had problems with respect to the custody of his kids.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
